17/03/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu says his ministry is working to include the Freedom and Democracy Congress of Kurdistan in the EU's list of terrorist organisations.
Recently, the Union added Turkey's Revolutionary People's Liberation Party and the Kurdistan Worker's Party to this list.
During a speech Saturday (15 March), Aksu added that a terrorist threat by separatists has been rendered ineffective.
(Anadolu Agency - 16/03/03)
